/* Useful information

Mandatory request parameters: redirect_uri, creditor, amount, purpose

The user can store the credentials within the first payments. For subsequent payments from the same debtor account of the user, only the Strong Customer Authentication for the payment initiation will be required. This means that the user does not need to enter the account credentials again.

Optional: "readout" request parameter to also get the account and transaction data of the users bank account. 
Default: []
Items Enum: "ACCOUNTS" "TRANSACTIONS"
Defines entries that shall be available for a readout after the payment has been initiated. Depending on the values provided the account information and transaction history of the source account can be retrieved. This will implicitly perform an account synchronization and might require additional challenges to be answered in the scope of the Strong Customer Authentication.

